increasing over the last years due to longer life expectancy, also resulting in 
a significant impact upon healthcare resources. The coronary sinus Reducer is a 
novel technology designed to improve the quality of life of these patients. The 
aim of this paper is to provide an overview of the available data regarding this 
new technology, along with the experience of the three centers that have 
performed the highest number of implants in Italy, focusing our attention on the 
clinical presentation of these complex patients and their follow-up.

